d to use if the SMTP server requires authentication.&#10;@var string" line="126" name="password" /><variable citdl="string" doc="Hostname or domain that will be sent to the remote SMTP server in the&#10;HELO / EHLO message.&#10;&#10;@var string" line="134" name="localhost" /><variable citdl="integer" doc="SMTP connection timeout value.  NULL indicates no timeout.&#10;&#10;@var integer" line="141" name="timeout" /><variable citdl="boolean" doc="Turn on Net_SMTP debugging?&#10;&#10;@var boolean $debug" line="148" name="debug" /><variable citdl="boolean" doc="Indicates whether or not the SMTP connection should persist over&#10;multiple calls to the send() method.&#10;&#10;@var boolean" line="156" name="persist" /><variable citdl="bool" doc="Use SMTP command pipelining (specified in RFC 2920) if the SMTP server&#10;supports it. This speeds up delivery over high-latency connections. By&#10;default, use the default value supplied by Net_SMTP.&#10;@var bool" line="164" name="pipelining" /><scope attributes="__ctor__" doc="Constructor.&#10;&#10;Instantiates a new Mail_smtp:: object based on the parameters&#10;passed in. It looks for the following parameters:&#10;    host        The server to connect to. Defaults to localhost.&#10;    port        The port to connect to. Defaults to 25.&#10;    auth        SMTP authentication.  Defaults to none.&#10;    username    The username to use for SMTP auth. No default.&#10;    password    The password to use for SMTP auth. No default.&#10;    localhost   The local hostname / domain. Defaults to localhost.&#10;    timeout     The SMTP connection timeout. Defaults to none.&#10;    verp        Whether to use VERP or not. Defaults to false.&#10;                DEPRECATED as of 1.2.0 (use setMailParams()).&#10;    debug       Activate SMTP debug mode? Defaults to false.&#10;    persist     Should the SMTP connection persist?&#10;    pipelining  Use SMTP command pipelining&#10;&#10;If a parameter is present in the $params array, it replaces the&#10;default.&#10;&#10;@param array Hash containing any parameters different from the&#10;             defaults.&#10;@access public" ilk="function" line="191" lineend="210" name="Mail_smtp" signature="Mail_smtp($params)"><variable ilk="argument" line="191" name="params" /></scope><scope doc="Destructor implementation to ensure that we disconnect from any&#10;potentially-alive persistent SMTP connections." ilk="function" line="216" lineend="219" name="_Mail_smtp" signature="_Mail_smtp()" /><scope doc="Implements Mail::send() function using SMTP.&#10;&#10;@param mixed $recipients Either a comma-seperated list of recipients&#10;             (RFC822 compliant), or an array of recipients,&#10;             each RFC822 valid. This may contain recipients not&#10;             specified in the headers, for Bcc:, resending&#10;             messages, etc.&#10;&#10;@param array $headers The array of headers to send with the mail, in an&#10;             associative array, where the array key is the&#10;             header name (e.g., 'Subject'), and the array value&#10;             is the header value (e.g., 'test'). The header&#10;             produced from those values would be 'Subject:&#10;             test'.&#10;&#10;@param string $body The full text of the message body, including any&#10;              MIME parts, etc.&#10;&#10;@return mixed Returns true on success, or a PEAR_Error&#10;              containing a descriptive error message on&#10;              failure.&#10;@access public" ilk="function" line="245" lineend="330" name="send" returns="mixed" signature="mixed send(mixed $recipients, array $headers, string $body)"><variable citdl="mixed" ilk="argument" line="245" name="recipients" /><variable citdl="array" ilk="argument" line="245" name="headers" /><variable citdl="string" ilk="argument" line="245" name="body" /><variable citdl="this.getSMTPObject()" line="248" name="result" /><variable attributes="__not_yet_defined__" line="281" name="val" /><variable attribu